Description: Helps companies work with college students / recent grads on short-term projects both to address immediate needs and improve hiring.
Full Description: Parker Dewey (www.ParkerDewey.com) helps companies utilize college students and recent grads for immediate support on short-term, professional assignments that may otherwise be neglected or completed by employees whose time is better spent elsewhere. These take under 5 minutes to post, and have zero obligation. In addition to the immediate benefits, companies can identify and evaluate job candidates, including those from diverse and underrepresented backgrounds, and authentically assess job skills, cultural fit, and non-cognitive traits (e.g. grit, communication, teamwork, etc.). For college students and recent grads, Parker Dewey provides the opportunity to demonstrate their skills and grit, explore careers, develop their networks, and generate income as they seek internships and full-time roles. Furthermore, these authentic, experiential learning opportunities complement in-class instruction, thereby improving academic performance and driving completion. As a result, career launchers graduate more job-ready, and have the perspective and experience to find a full-time role with the right skill and cultural fit. Using data from these projects, Parker Dewey also provides insights to college and university faculty so that they can better align curriculum with job skills demanded by companies. In addition, these academic institutions can more effectively engage alumni and professors as mentors, counsel students on career options, and support existing and / or prospective corporate recruiters. Parker Dewey made it really easy for everyone to use the platform. It takes under five minutes to post a project (including setting the price and due date), career launchers apply only to those assignments that interest them, and companies select who they think is the best fit. And since we are not a staffing or recruiting firm, there are no administrative burdens associated with these “micro-internships” or fees if a company wants to directly hire someone.

Description: Otomagnetics produces a magnetic injection delivery system that can deliver therapy to few parts of the body.
Full Description: Otomagnetics LLC, a University of Maryland College Park spin-out, is developing a non-invasive method to effectively deliver drugs and other therapeutic payloads to the inner and middle ear.,The inner ear is behind the blood-labyrinth barrier – vessels that supply blood to the inner ear have walls that are impermeable to most drug molecules, and thus it is a challenge to deliver therapy to treat inner ear diseases. In an animal model, Otomagnetics’ proprietary magnetic injection system has demonstrated drug delivery to the inner ear, and has shown improved dosing and therapeutic effect in preclinical models of tinnitus and noise-induced hearing loss. In an animal model, Otomagnetics’ technology has further shown drug delivery to the middle ear, without the need to puncture the ear drum. Magnetic delivery to the middle ear is being considered as a potential non-invasive treatment option for otitis media (middle ear infections). Note: Otomagnetics products are experimental, and not approved by the FDA for human use.

Description: Digi-Me operates in the staffing and recruiting, also termed talent acquisition, segment of the human resources technology market.
Full Description: Digi-Me operates in the staffing and recruiting, also termed talent acquisition, segment of the human resources technology market. There are many segments of the U.S. talent acquisition market. The market is growing in many segments including staffing firms, which are expected to achieve $125 billion in revenue in 2015. One of the largest growing segments in the talent acquisition market are the recruitment software providers, which will grow to $3 billion in 2015 with growth rates of 14.3% over the past 5 years. Market experts estimate that the U.S. represents approximately one-third of the world market and that the Global Talent Acquisition Market exceeds $400 billion (Market Line).    Digi-Me believes that all players in the talent acquisition market – whether employers or their software and service providers – will benefit from the use of video for employment advertising and employer branding. Because Digi-Me’s target customers and service providers are global themselves, and because its cloud-based technology platform is global and completely scalable as well, management believes Digi-Me is capable of addressing the global talent acquisition market. Management estimates its video services potentially constitute 10% of the talent acquisition market, of which an estimated 10% is actually reachable by Digi-Me, resulting in a global, addressable market opportunity of $4 billion.    To provide perspective, the development of internet-based employment services enabled employers to eliminate 92% of newsprint classified ads from 2000 -2009, as classified ad spending dropped from $8.5 billion to $750 million. The Company expects rapid adoption of video capabilities to complement internet text postings because of dominant trends in consumer preferences driven by technology: high penetration of smart mobile devices, video streaming, social media, and the dramatic increase in video consumption among all demographics.

Description: Retalent builds predictive hiring models to help companies and candidates find a better match
Full Description: Retalent is a talent evaluation tool to better match candidates to jobs. We believe the resume is an inadequate representation of who should be interviewed, especially when recruiters have less time than ever to review the increasing number of candidates for every job. What really matters is how an employee performs in their role, which is a function of their behaviors. To better predict how well a candidate will perform in a role, we use realistic simulations to assess behavioral traits. The traits of each candidate are compared with traits of top performing employees to make a better match. The app and website provide a map of nearby caregivers available now to assist families with their loved ones.  In the case of nursing homes and assisted living facilities, RestUp has streamlined its hiring process and can assist facilities with staffing shortages, emergency shift needs, and regular PRN needs. A timely background check is done on each and every caregiver that accepts a shift request. And a rating system is used, so that you can see what other facilities and families have said about the caregiver. Each caregiver's profile can be integrated with that of his or her Facebook or LinkedIn profile. Additionally, an option to link to a video introduction is available.  All payments are handled via the app, so neither party needs to worry about exchanging money or financial information.  RestUp uses the secure payment processing service Stripe, with easy withdrawal from the user’s bank account. For ease in determining the final bill charged to the user, a time-clock is used.  Facilities are invoiced weekly. In 2020, RestUp has seen exponential growth in its facility staffing side of the platform.

Full Description: RPh on the Go is a healthcare staffing company that focuses solely on pharmacy. RPh on the Go’s experienced recruiting staff and targeted recruiting approach allow them to help their customers expand their businesses by matching the right pharmacy personnel to staff upcoming growth markets. The staffing company’s rigorous approval process ensures that every pharmacist they place is of the highest caliber. Their candidate approval process includes: a 10 panel drug screening (5 or 12 panel available upon client request), current medical review and background checks, HIPAA compliance training and verification, in-depth candidate interviews, license status and standing verification on monthly basis, OIG and state board checks verified on monthly basis, ongoing Performance Evaluations (PEs) and a quality Seal review and rating. RPh on the Go has become the largest agency of their kind because they strive to do things right. Not only does the company employ more pharmacists than any pharmacy agency in the world, but they also have a broader base of knowledge and a far deeper understanding of the way pharmacies work.

MBI also provides technical consultation support to help teams that may need high-level experts to step in and provide technical review of the most critical projects. Almost all staffing companies claim the same differentiators and add value, but MBI truly is a different type of company in terms of the approach we take to ensuring we can meet the customer's very specific needs. The most profound differentiator is that MBI brings a group of highly technical staff to the very first meeting, not salesmen. Bringing the right people to the initial discussion, is hyper critical due to the fact that most IT teams are under intense pressure to deliver against very high expectations, and any steps taken to expedite the delivery of quality professionals is a step in the right direction. Above all, MBI wants any potential customer to sense both simplicity in how to get the process underway, and we want to reflect absolute professionalism in our ability to deliver quality IT resources.

In 2009, TheraStaff merged with The Eastridge Group of Staffing Companies founded in 1972 by Robert Svet to become TheraStaff LLC. Eastridge is one of the nation’s largest privately held staffing companies, backed by nearly 40 years of staffing expertise and a network of colleagues adding value and depth to rehabilitation staffing services. As a specialty division of Eastridge, clients of TheraStaff LLC have access to a multitude of workforce resources, including a sister medical staffing division that places Medical administrative support, clinicians such as physician assistants, nurses practitioners and more. Our family of staffing companies also includes a technology staffing division that’s experienced in the healthcare field, and a human resources staffing division with years of expertise in supporting the medical field. We’re proud of the work we do and the area of medicine we support.
